NAME
  vexec - execute command inside a context
SYNOPSIS
  vexec [-cfi] [-x xid] -- [cmd] [args]
DESCRIPTION
  vexec is used to execute the command cmd passing it args as arguments in an
  already existing context and its namespace.
OPTIONS
    -c       chroot to current directory
    -f       Fork into background before executing cmd
    -i       Make cmd the general process reaper for the context (aka initpid)
    -x xid   Context ID
EXAMPLE
  Execute bash in context '123' (this is what 'vserver enter [name]' does)

      $ vexec -x 123 -- /bin/bash
SEE ALSO
  vserver(8)
